<DOC><DOCNO> AP881004-0075 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-04-88 0952EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Spain-Shooting     10-04 0200</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Spain-Shooting,0206</SECOND><HEAD>Policeman Killed While Guarding Government Office</HEAD><DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two men and a woman stormed a governmentoffice in central Madrid today, shooting and killing a policemanand injuring three other people, police said.   The assailants took the policeman's gun as he stood guardoutside the ground-floor office, then used it to shoot the officertwice in the head, Spanish National Radio reported. The shootingtook place at 9:40 a.m. on the busy street of Santa Engracia,police said.   One of the attackers fired at a second policeman, grazing him inthe leg, and at a man and a woman, who also were brushed by thebullets but were not seriously injured, police said.   The two men were accompanied by a woman, police said. The threefled on foot after grabbing several blank personal identificationcards, police said.   The police officer, Bernardino Ortega Ramsad, 47, was dead onarrival at Red Cross Hospital, the hospital reported.   There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the attack.   In the past, members of the Basque separatist organization ETAhave killed policemen and military officers as part of theirviolent 20-year campaign for independence of the northern Basqueregion.</TEXT></DOC>